irubin elevation greater than 2 times ULN, aminotransferase elevations are greater than 8 times ULN, or aminotransferase elevations persist beyond 2 weeks.', 'Synergism', 'The use of bedaquiline with other potentially hepatotoxic agents should be avoided whenever possible (e.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/173657/', '', 'Pertuzumab, Olaparib, Tisagenlecleucel, Aminolevulinic acid, Omacetaxine mepesuccinate, Altretamine, Enasidenib, Porfimer sodium, Niraparib, Selinexor, Aflibercept, More', 'Capreomycin, Pyrazinamide, Rifamycin, Sulfamethoxazole, Streptomycin, Rifampicin, Cycloserine, Rifabutin, Isoniazid, Ethambutol, Ethionamide, More', 1767369485);
